-- Century to Acquire Kentucky Aluminum Smelter From Rio Tinto
-- B y   S o n j a   E l m q u i s t
-- 2013-04-29T13:41:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-29/century-to-acquire-kentucky-aluminum-smelter-from-rio-tinto.html
  Century Aluminum Co. (CENX) , the third-
largest U.S. producer of the metal by market value, said it
agreed to buy the Sebree smelter in Kentucky from Rio Tinto
Group for $61 million.  Rio will retain all historical environmental liabilities
and will fully fund the pension plan being assumed by the buyer,
Monterey, California-based Century said today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sonja Elmquist in  New York  at 
